WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:06.000
If you camp in the desert southwest, you already know nights can still feel brutal inside a tent.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.000
I tested five portable camping fans on medium speed until each battery died.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Two brands hit their advertised runtime, but three quit early and got noticeably louder after hour four.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:24.000
The clip-on model moved the most air, yet the motor whine made it hard to sleep unless you run it on low.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:30.000
For car camping, the folding tripod fan was the most stable and the easiest to aim at your sleeping bag.
